article.story: ROCK HILL, S.C. -- — Drew Pember scored 29 points as UNC Asheville knocked off Winthrop 82-77 on Thursday night. The loss knocked the Eagles out of a share of first place in the Big South Conference. Pember added 13 rebounds for the Bulldogs (12-8, 4-1). Josh Banks was 4 of 7 shooting, including 2 for 3 from 3-point range, and went 4 for 5 from the line to add 14 points. Caleb Burgess had 12 points and was 5 of 6 shooting and 0 of 4 from the free throw line. Kelton Talford led the Eagles (13-7, 4-1) in scoring, finishing with 21 points and 10 rebounds. Winthrop also got 20 points and four assists from Nick Johnson. KJ Doucet also recorded nine points and four steals. The Eagles ended a five-game winning streak with the loss. UNC Asheville's next game is Wednesday against Radford at home. Winthrop visits Gardner-Webb on Saturday. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
